rComments: I thought that this class is hard. In discussion, we work as a group, and most of the time I understand the material given. Butit does not show in my exams. Every exam just depresses me to find out I am going to fail this class. I used my notes, book, but I had no time to meet the professor to get help. Studying early and old test did not help.

Lynne Miller,  if you think you are an awesome professor, there is no need to write on this website.  I think you should seriously look over these comments and try to learn from them.  I agree these comments are quite harsh.  However, we won't make these comments up if we like you and think you are an awesone professor.
An extremely hard class. If you don't read the text or attend SI office hours it will be difficult. Her exams were extremely hard, so the curves were pretty huge.

She is very nice and will teach you everything you need to know about the subject. People are pissed off because they didnt stay on top of everything and all that and thats reasonable because the online lectures are always there. I did 8 in 3 days and thats annoying so keep up do the exams and talk to her about any problems.

I'm not sure where all this is coming from! I think I am an awesome professor! Sure my exams may be so hard that God himself couldn't do them, but what's the point in having exams that mortals can complete in one and a half hours?

well it's almost over and what can i say...i'm not happy with the amount of o-chem i learned in this class. my exam average so far has been about a 50 percent and that's probably gonna be a B or a C, possibly an A if im lucky with the curve. what kind of class gives an A to someone who only knows 2/3rds of the material? i was duped this semester.

I feel as if orgo lectures were useless this year. most of my success came from self study and reading other materials. i strongly feel that very important concepts in this class are merely glossed over in the lectures and book readings you CANNOT rely on the class materials to do well. i guarantee you will fail if you do just that.

Lynne Miller is NOT a good professor.  She purposely writes exams to bring people's grades down.  Only those who naturally understand organic chemistry exceed in her class because she does little to teach it.  SI leaders deserve all credit for anyone learning anything in this class.
No Comments

Lynne Miller is a horrible professor.  Who lets this lady teach?  The University should really look into how poor of a job she's doing- any positive reviews of her on this website were probably written by her family members (or herself) because anyone whose taken a class with her knows how awful she truly is.  Take orgo with another professor.

Dr. Miller is one of the best chemistry teachers I have had. She takes hard concepts and makes them easier to understand. She is very clear and you can tell she chooses her wording very carefully. Sure, this class is a lot of work, but if you are willing to put in the effort I guarantee it will be worth it. If you are not, orgo may not be for you.

Might be the worst teacher in the history of this school.  Seems nice at first, but as the semester goes on she finds ways to make you hate her.  Lectures are terribly taught/explained and she always sounds like she is out of breath which is irritating.

I had her for 232 and 233 this summer, and I thought she was cool at first, but after this, I really don't think so.  She rarely responds to emails, and there was a wrong answer on the key for our first exam, but she refused to go back and regrade the exams! So, the people who know their stuff got it wrong and the people that don't know their stuff

Absolutely horrible. She changed the exam format in the middle of the semester without letting us know. I got a 58 out of 150 points and I was 1 point away from an A. Her lectures tell you all sorts of useless crap and don't actually teach you anything. The SI leaders should be teaching the class because I learned EVERYTHING from them.

Dishonest, Disorganized Had her kids at offices hours and would not unlock door while I waited outside. said she was having "mommy time" Worst teacher I have ever had. Needs to be fired ASAP. My younger sister is attending a different college because of horror stories regarding her.

I don't think she is bad at all. She's really clear and good at keeping you focused when she lectures at 8am. She's ALWAYS available when you need her. Take Moore and then you can complain. His exams are DIFFICULT and impossible. Her exams are difficult as well, but hey which science in this place is not?

Lynn Miller is the worst professor at the University of Illinois. To all students enrolled in her course, definitely drop it and take it with another professor! She is horribly unorganized and lied to me about my grade. She wont help you with anything and she posts final grades on the website after they've been locked in. Stay away from her...

The lab lecture was useless and the course was poorly run. Grades were never posted on time. It took her two weeks to post our final grades, and the final exam was 28 questions multiple choice AND SOME OF THE QUESTIONS WERE WORTH EIGHT POINTS because the test was out of 150.

Good lecturer but every other aspect of the lab class was a mess. Class power points always posted late, and test and lab grades always took weeks to come online. I would highly not recommend her because you will get so constantly frustrated for broken promises on her part.

At the beginning of the year she seemed very friendly and helpful. As the semester progressed she wasnt nearly as nice and she wouldnt get back to the students about questions. She isnt very well organized either. One good point was that she was very straight to the point in the lab lectures so we never had to stay for all 50minutes for lab lecture
